		<a href="MB_editmsg.asp?FID=64&FN=Magician&SID=7&SN=EverQuest&TID=1837470&TN=Mage+Partner%3F&CAT=Classes&SURL=http%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Eeverlore%2Ecom&MSID=1878603&PL=4">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/edit.gif" border="0" alt="Edit/Delete Message" width="18" height="13"></a>
		
		</font>
		<hr size="1">What you have to ask yourself is "How dexerious am I?<BR>What type of fighting do I want to do?  Do I want to be able to travel?" Have to ask yourself questions like that....</P><P>This is why:</P><P>Magician / Bard combo is excellent. Bards, heal, mez, help with mana just as well as an enchanter, + better then Sow travelling speed etc etc etc...BUT it takes using one hand constantly to play a bard, not including if you want to use your mouse to target, move etc. And if you want to be a good bard, it needs all your attention to do so, take it from me I have a 37 bard as well as a 60 magician.</P><P>Your best bet is a healer / magician combo. </P><P>Clerics to me are boring, also have a lv 22. Sit, heal, sit heal, sit, heal...Bahhh ! Oh a rez when you get high enough, and great buffs....but thats about it.</P><P>Druids are okay, but heals suck until high 50's. Get Sow, transport for your team, but if you get luclin and PoP add-ons you can use them to get around. Nice buffs, not as good as a shaman in my opinion though.</P><P>Magician / Warrior, Monk Tank type...Who is gonna heal your team? Mages only get pet heals, and tanks can do nothing but fight.</P><P>Enchanter / Magician: Big deal...some buffs, and a mez, a terrible pet for enchanters, again no healer, and it your pet gets in trouble you can't expect the enchanter to tank much.</P><P>Shaman / Magician: now this is another great combo...Shamans have great buffs, heals, get a pet that isnt to bad, they can tank some. Sow spells etc etc.</P><P>Necro / Mage: 2 pets are nice...2 people casting, great damage per second here, but again who heals the pets?  Who buffs? who helps with anything but dealing damage?...Yeah necros can heal some, and help with mana gain, but they have to lose thier own to do so.</P><P>Mage / Wizard ? NOT</P><P>If you can to the Mage/ Bard go for it, but I doubt it...I play a great Mage, and a great bard but I could never do both sucessfully all the time, nor as good as when I play them seperately.  Go with a good healer combo...That would be your best bet.</P><P>GL =),<BR>Ryeed<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
	</font>
	</td>
